<law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection amended="yes" chaptername="Crimes And Punishments" id="id13" statutenumber="28-106"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>28-106</statuteno><catchline id="id16">Misdemeanors; classification of penalties; sentences; where served.</catchline><para>(1) For purposes of the Nebraska Criminal Code and any statute passed by the Legislature after the date of passage of the code, misdemeanors are divided into seven classes which are distinguished from one another by the following penalties which are authorized upon conviction:</para><para><table frame="none"><tgroup cols="2"><?PubTbl tgroup clmarg="0.00pt" crmarg="0.00pt" ctmarg="0.00pt" cbmarg="2.10pt"?><colspec align="right" colname="col1" colwidth="1" /><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.61" /><tbody><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0">Class I misdemeanor........</entry><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — not more than one year</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">imprisonment, or one thousand dollars</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">fine, or both</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.32in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Minimum — none</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0">Class II misdemeanor.......</entry><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — six months imprisonment, or</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">one thousand dollars fine, or both</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Minimum — none</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0">Class III misdemeanor......</entry><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — three months imprisonment,</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">or five hundred dollars fine, or both</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Minimum — none</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0">Class IIIA misdemeanor.....</entry><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — seven days imprisonment, five</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">hundred dollars fine, or both</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Minimum — none</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0">Class IV misdemeanor.......</entry><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — no imprisonment, five</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">hundred dollars fine</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Minimum — none</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0">Class V misdemeanor........</entry><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — no imprisonment, one</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">hundred dollars fine</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Minimum — none</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0">Class W misdemeanor.......</entry><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Driving under the influence or implied</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">consent</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">First conviction </entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — sixty days imprisonment and</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">five hundred dollars fine</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Mandatory minimum — seven days</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">imprisonment and five hundred dollars</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">fine</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Second conviction</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — six months imprisonment and</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">five hundred dollars fine</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Mandatory minimum — thirty days</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">imprisonment and five hundred dollars</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">fine</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Third conviction </entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Maximum — one year imprisonment and</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">one thousand dollars fine</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">Mandatory minimum — ninety days</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">imprisonment</entry></row><row><?PubTbl row rht="0.31in"?><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0" /><entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">and one thousand dollars fine</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></para><para>(2) Sentences of imprisonment in misdemeanor cases shall be served in the county jail, except that such sentences may be served in institutions under the jurisdiction of the Department of Correctional Services if the sentence is to be served concurrently or consecutively with a term for conviction of a felony and the combined sentences total a term of one year or more. A determinate sentence shall be imposed for a misdemeanor if the sentence is to be served concurrently or consecutively with a determinate sentence for a Class III, IIIA, or IV felony.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1977, LB 38, &#167; 6; </para><para>Laws 1982, LB 568, &#167; 1; </para><para>Laws 1986, LB 153, &#167; 1; </para><para>Laws 1992, LB 291, &#167; 1; </para><para>Laws 1998, LB 309, &#167; 1; </para><para>Laws 2002, LB 82, &#167; 3; </para><para>Laws 2005, LB 594, &#167; 1; </para><para>Laws 2011, LB675, &#167; 1; </para><para>Laws 2015, LB605, &#167; 7; </para><para>Laws 2016, LB1094, &#167; 3. </para><effectivedate>April 20, 2016</effectivedate></source><annotation><para>The proper determination of punishment for fourth offense driving under the influence of an alcoholic liquor or drug is governed by subsection (1) of this section and not by section 28-107(3). State v. Schultz, 252 Neb. 746, 566 N.W.2d 739 (1997).</para><para>For a Class III misdemeanor, a sentence of five days in jail with a fine of three hundred dollars is within the statutory maximum and will not be disturbed on appeal absent an abuse of discretion. State v. Rosenberry, 209 Neb. 383, 307 N.W.2d 823 (1981).</para></annotation></law>
